<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-07-04T11:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-07-04T11:00:00-05:00" n="432" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d432">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">811.20 Defense (M)/7573: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Ecuador</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Long</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Quito</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-07-04T11:00:00-05:00">July 4,
                                    1942—11 a.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received 3:30 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>550. My telegram No. 546, July 3, 9 a.m.<note n="77" xml:id="d432fn77">Not printed.</note> I am confidentially informed that at last
                            night’s Cabinet Council Meeting an agreement is said to have been
                            reached which changes the rubber agreement substantially in favor of
                            Ecuador. As today is a holiday we do not expect details until
                            Monday.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Long</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>